spec: multiprocessing_extra131
version: ">=3.9"
backend: python_module(multiprocessing)

docs: https://docs.python.org/3/library/multiprocessing.html

provenance:
  derived_from:
    - "https://docs.python.org/3/library/multiprocessing.html — Python multiprocessing module documentation"
    - "Test vectors verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-11"
  not_derived_from:
    - "CPython source: Lib/multiprocessing/pool.py"
  notes:
    - "This spec covers: wave 256 theme — multiprocessing.pool.Pool method qualnames and class identity. NEW in extra131: multiprocessing.pool.Pool.__init__.__qualname__=='Pool.__init__' (len=13); multiprocessing.pool.Pool.apply.__qualname__=='Pool.apply' (len=10); multiprocessing.pool.Pool.map.__qualname__=='Pool.map' (len=8); multiprocessing.pool.Pool.close.__qualname__=='Pool.close' (len=10); multiprocessing.pool.Pool.terminate.__qualname__=='Pool.terminate' (len=14); multiprocessing.pool.Pool.apply_async.__qualname__=='Pool.apply_async' (len=16); multiprocessing.pool.Pool.map_async.__qualname__=='Pool.map_async' (len=14); multiprocessing.pool.Pool.starmap.__qualname__=='Pool.starmap' (len=12); multiprocessing.pool.Pool.__bases__[0].__name__=='object'; multiprocessing.pool.Pool.__mro__.__len__()==2; multiprocessing.pool.__name__=='multiprocessing.pool' (len=20). All verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-11."
    - "multiprocessing.pool.Pool.__bases__[0].__name__ == 'object'. Pool inherits directly from object with no intermediate base classes, giving the minimal 2-element MRO [Pool, object]. Verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-11."
    - "multiprocessing.pool.__name__ == 'multiprocessing.pool' (len=20). The submodule name is 20 chars: 'multiprocessing'=15 + '.'=1 + 'pool'=4 = 20. Verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-11."
    - "multiprocessing.pool.Pool.terminate.__qualname__ == 'Pool.terminate' (len=14). This is the longest single-word method qualname among the Pool methods in this spec. Verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-11."
    - "All expected values verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-11."
  created_at: "2026-04-11T00:00:00Z"

